result.name: Jazz Ramen

reviews.text: The ramen is average tasting, but not served hot enough and only warm. Some interesting side dishes like tofu. This is a small shop with street views only. Pricing is moderate. Could be allot better, but unfortunately it is getting worse.
Best ramen I've had in a long time. Must try spicy soup base!
Stable quality, now daughter in charge

Service is not good, no greeting on entry or thanks on leaving, my assigned seat at the end of the bar was right next to the entrance to the kitchen which meant constantly being brushed & having staff stretching hands over my head for stuff as I was eating (free tables were available but they wanted me at the bar). They also don't trust their patrons so you have to pay on ordering instead of after the meal. The best thing about the ramen was the hot soup; the noodles were okay but looked/tatsed like Chinese noodles, and the Jazz special was uninspiring. The tofu side dish was quite hard. Cross this one off my list, there are much better places to spend your money in Fanling.
Cozy small places for Raman lover around this district.
